HEADWORD: Midgut
<hw>Mid"gut`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Mid</ets>, a. +
<ets>gut</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The middle part of the
alimentary canal from the stomach, or entrance of the bile duct, to, or
including, the large intestine.</def>⟦br⟧
